- bug #55503: Jobs should not be able to be removed in completing status
- bug #55952: postprocess_hook never called for failed jobs

NOTICE: added a new hook postprocess_failed() which is only called from completing->failed, this 
avoids recursion with existing postprocess() hooks (if they attempt to fail the job) and will allow 
to separate the two functionalities more cleanly

- bug #64514: ApplicationConfigurationError triggers WARNING instead of ERROR -level messages
- bug #67876: Re-running the merger should be more straightforward
- bug #53751: Release reported wrong when checking out from SVN
- bug #68547: A function to monitor some jobs by hand?

The last bugfix introduces a new (experimental) feature -> ability to monitor an arbitrary slice of 
jobs i.e. to perform monitoring on a subset of jobs. Recipe: 

1) run ganga with monitoring disabled 
ganga -o[PollThread]autostart=False 

2) to update status of last 4 jobs do this: 
runMonitoring(jobs=jobs[-4:]) 

You may also change the jobs slice in the subsequent call to runMonitoring(jobs=other_job_slice)


